**Rule File System — Build Notes**

**File structure**

```
repo-root/
├── .rules.md          ← minimal global baseline
├── payments/
│   └── .rules.md
├── billing/
│   └── .rules.md
│   └── subscriptions/
│       └── .rules.md
```

**How rules are loaded** Walk up the directory tree from the file being worked on, collect every `.rules.md` found, concatenate root-first, inject into agent context. ~30-50 lines of code.

python

```python
def collect_rules(file_path, repo_root):
    rules = []
    path = Path(file_path).parent
    while True:
        rule_file = path / ".rules.md"
        if rule_file.exists():
            rules.append(rule_file.read_text())
        if path == repo_root:
            break
        path = path.parent
    return "\n\n".join(reversed(rules))
```

**Storage** AWS CodeCommit. VPC-internal, IAM auth, no egress fees. Cloned onto the EC2 devbox at run start. Devbox is destroyed after the run. CodeCommit is the permanent source of truth.****
